President Biden has announced his intention to nominate Dr. Monica Bertagnolli as the Director of the National Institutes of Health (NIH). Dr. Bertagnolli, who currently serves as the Director of the National Cancer Institute (NCI), is a respected surgical oncologist, cancer researcher, educator, and physician-leader. President Biden praised Dr. Bertagnolli's career and her commitment to improving cancer prevention and treatment for patients, as well as ensuring access to quality care for all communities. Dr. Bertagnolli has been involved in clinical and research oncology and has championed initiatives to transform the data infrastructure for cancer research. She is a member of the National Academy of Medicine and has held leadership positions in various medical organizations. The nomination has been widely celebrated by physician and research leaders, patient groups, and health advocates, who believe that Dr. Bertagnolli's expertise and leadership will ensure that the NIH continues to be at the forefront of biomedical innovation and improving the health of the American people.